@node Overview
@chapter Overview

clamdscan-tools provides two command-line programs:

@itemize @bullet
@item @command{clamdscan-progress} runs scans with a progress indicator, resumable state files and configurable exclusions.
@item @command{clamdscan-watch} shows or follows the logs produced by completed or active scans.
@end itemize

The package is intended for Debian systems and integrates with the standard
filesystem layout for binaries, configuration, logs and Info documentation.

@node Installation
@chapter Installation

Install the binary package with:

@example
sudo apt install ./clamdscan-tools_0.1.0_all.deb
@end example

Remove it with:

@example
sudo apt remove clamdscan-tools
@end example

Purge the package, including configuration files managed by dpkg, with:

@example
sudo apt purge clamdscan-tools
@end example

